article.headline: Bucknell 85, Navy 77
article.story: LEWISBURG, Pa. (AP) -- Justin Castleberry scored 19 points and three other Bucknell players were in double figures as the Bison came from behind to beat Navy 85-77 on Friday night. Jason Vegotsky scored 14 points, John Griffin had 13 and Stephen Tyree contributed 10 for Bucknell (6-9, 1-0 Patriot League). Greg Sprink scored 26 points and Kaleo Kina had 24 for Navy (7-9, 0-1). Navy had a 46-39 lead at the half as Kina scored 17 points and Sprink had 16 in the period. But Bucknell went on an 18-9 run to start the second half, taking a 57-55 lead on Darryl Shazier's layup with 10:32 remaining. Vegotsky's 3-pointer gave the Bison a 10-point lead, 66-56, with 7:03 left in the game.
